28:T25a2,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How many people have my exact name worldwide right now?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Type your first name into the checker above to see a live estimate of global bearers, based on 100M+ records from 80+ countries. Most common English first names have between 500,000 and 10 million living bearers worldwide."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many people share my first name in the United States?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"We combine U.S. Social Security Administration birth records (1880–present) with actuarial life tables to estimate how many living Americans share your first name. Results appear in under 1 second with no signup."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Am I the only person in the world with my name?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"For truly unique first-name + surname combinations, yes — our tool can flag a name as 'likely unique' (fewer than 5 estimated bearers). Enter your full name to check if you may be the only one."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is it possible that no one else has my exact full name?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Roughly 1 in 8 full-name combinations in the U.S. are estimated to be unique. Add your surname in the optional field to see whether your first + last name combination is one-of-a-kind."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many babies were born with my name last year?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Our popularity checker shows year-by-year birth counts back to 1880 and forward to the most recent release (typically prior year). You'll see exact annual figures for the U.S., UK, and major English-speaking countries."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which country has the most people with my first name?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"After you search a name, the results page lists the top 10 countries by estimated living bearers, so you'll see instantly whether your name is most common in the US, India, Brazil, Nigeria, or elsewhere."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is my name rarer than the average American name?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The average U.S. first name is held by about 45,000 living people. If your name has fewer bearers, it's rarer than average. Our tool shows a percentile rarity score so you can compare against the full U.S. population."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is my name more common than Michael or Jennifer?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Michael (~4.4M living U.S. bearers) and Jennifer (~1.5M) are benchmark 'very common' names. Search your name to see a side-by-side bearer count against these anchors."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does my name rank among the top 1000 most popular names?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"If your name is in the top 1,000, we display its exact rank (e.g. #247) plus how that rank has changed decade by decade since 1880."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is my name considered rare, uncommon, common, or very common?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"We label every name with a rarity tier: Very Common (top 100), Common (top 1,000), Uncommon (top 10,000), Rare (under 1 in 100,000 bearers), or Ultra-Rare (fewer than 100 bearers globally)."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does the popularity of my name compare to my parents' generation?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Our decade-by-decade popularity chart shows whether your name peaked in the 1950s, 1980s, or today — so you can see exactly how your name's popularity compares to when your parents were born."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Which is rarer — my first name or my last name?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Enter both your first name and surname. The results page shows separate rarity scores and bearer estimates for each, so you can compare which one makes you more unique."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How accurate is the data behind your name popularity checker?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"For common names in well-documented countries (US, UK, Canada, Australia), our estimates are accurate within ±5%. For rarer names or countries with less comprehensive records, accuracy ranges from ±10% to ±25%. Each estimate includes a confidence score."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Where do you get your name data from and can I trust it?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"We aggregate data from official government sources: the U.S. SSA (350M+ records since 1880), UK ONS, Statistics Canada, Australian ABS, Eurostat, and peer-reviewed academic research. All sources are cited on our Methodology page."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why do different name checker tools give different numbers?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Different sites use different data sources, time periods, and methodologies. Some only count current-year births; we estimate total living bearers using actuarial survival modeling. Some use only U.S. data; we aggregate globally across 80+ countries."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How often do you update your name frequency database?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"We refresh our core dataset quarterly, incorporating newly released birth registration data. Most countries release annual name data with a 6–18 month lag, so our figures are typically current to within a year."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I really find out how many people have my name in 1 second?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Results are pre-computed and served from an indexed database, so you'll see your name's bearer count, rarity score, and global distribution in well under 1 second — no signup, no waiting, no email required."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is the result an exact number or an estimate?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"For U.S. first names, we use SSA-recorded counts plus survival modeling — these are point estimates with ±5% confidence. Global numbers are always estimates because not every country publishes full name data."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What's the best free tool to check how many people share my name?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"HowManyOfMe.co is free, requires no signup, and covers 100M+ name records across 80+ countries — the most comprehensive free tool available. Type your name into the search bar above to try it now."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do I have to sign up or enter my email to use this name checker?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. The tool is 100% free with zero signup, no email required, and no download. Just type your first name and get instant results."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I check how many people have my name without downloading an app?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes — everything runs in your browser. No app, no install, no account. Works on phone, tablet, and desktop."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is my name stored or tracked when I search?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. We do not store, log, or associate your name search with any personal identifier. Searches are anonymous and your privacy is protected."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I use this name checker on my phone?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes — our tool is fully mobile-optimized. Search, see rarity scores, and browse the A–Z name directory on any device."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are there voice-assistant friendly queries I can ask about my name?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. You can ask voice assistants things like 'how many people have my name' or 'is my name rare' and our pages are structured for AI answer engines and AI overviews."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many people have my full name including my surname?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Add your last name in the optional field. We'll estimate how many people share your exact first + last name combination using linked birth and census records."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I check how many people share my name with a specific middle name?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Middle name support is limited — most public records index first + last name. You can, however, check each name separately and multiply approximate frequencies for a rough middle-name combo estimate."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many people have the same first and last name as me in my country?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Our country filter lets you narrow a full-name search to a specific country (e.g. 'how many John Smiths live in the UK'), returning a country-specific bearer estimate."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many people in my age group share my name?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Our decade-by-decade breakdown shows how many people in each birth-year cohort were given your name, so you can see how many people your age share your name specifically."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I check how rare my name is for my gender?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Every name page shows a gender split percentage (e.g. 97% female / 3% male) so you can see whether your name is rare for your specific gender."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many people share my name and were born in the same decade as me?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Enter your name and check the historical popularity chart — it shows the exact number of bearers born in the 1980s, 1990s, 2000s, 2010s, and 2020s, so you can isolate your own cohort."}}]}24:["$","$1","c",{"children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-background","children":[[["$","script","0",{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"WebSite\",\"name\":\"HowManyOfMe\",\"url\":\"https://howmanyofme.co\",\"potentialAction\":{\"@type\":\"SearchAction\",\"target\":\"https://howmanyofme.co/name/{search_term_string}\",\"query-input\":\"required name=search_term_string\"}}"}}],["$","script","1",{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$28"}}]],"$L29","$L2a","$L2b","$L2c","$L2d"]}],null,"$L2e"]}]
